      <div class="msgContentFrame">I tend to use for items that need to be &quot;ground down&quot;, such as rocks into gems, or bone into ornaments.  It seems to work very well for things like at.  I've also noticed you are more likely to get more of an item (if you are making parts) by using the secondary tool, and +1 - +3 version of an item if you are using the primary tool, although this seems to vary. <br /> <br />On a somewhat related note, does anyone know the recipe to create the next tier of the secondary goldsmith tool?  I can't find it :-(</div>
